            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1719390984299-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1719390984299-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!), then dissolve in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>soy sauce </strong>and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> – this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>coconut stock </strong>and<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until a thick sauce remains and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1719390988290-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1719390988290-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1719390988290-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1719390988290-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1719390988290-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the curry is cooking, chop the <strong>reserved coriander leaves</strong> roughly</p><p>Once the chicken is cooked, transfer to a clean board and shred it apart, using two forks – this technique is known as ‘pulling’</p><p>Return the <strong>pulled chicken</strong> to the pan and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your<strong> Sri Lankan-style free range chicken curry</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1719390992742-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1719390992742-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1719390992742-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1719390992742-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1719390992742-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Sri Lankan-style free range chicken curry</strong> over the <strong>basmati rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with your <strong>crispy onions</strong> and <strong>chopped coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
